race.comment: MOONLIGHT DREAM (2) resumes, and now in the Brett Mallyon yard. Showed a stack of ability on the provincial and city tracks when last in work. Fitted with a good trial win over 900m here. Nose roll goes on from the inside gate. Ticks a few boxes. COMPLAISANCE (5) near her top for this and had excuses from the wide gate when a fading eighth over 1400m at Gundagai. Finds an easier race and the lone win came at this track and trip. Has the ability to take care of this field. COLOMBIANO (9) struggled to see the 1400m out when fifth at Corowa. Just over a month between runs for this and no surprise to see her return to the winner's circle. EXTRIO (10) comes out of a strong contest at her third race start when a fading sixth over 1100m at Gundagai. Worth another chance.NEPELA (4) is struggling to draw a low gate. On the quick backup and assess on the good second two-back at Wodonga.
